# Example local Worker variables for `wrangler dev`.
#
# Copy this file to `.dev.vars` (which is git-ignored) and fill in values as
# needed. `.dev.vars` must NEVER be committed. Only non-secret local overrides
# belong here today; real secrets are set with `wrangler secret put` against a
# deployed environment, never stored in the repository.

# Environment label surfaced by the /health endpoint. One of:
# development | preview | staging | production
ENVIRONMENT="development"

# FND-03 workspace isolation (ADR-010): the server-side workspace scope resolved
# at the composition boundary. This is trusted server-side CONFIGURATION, not a
# secret, and never comes from a request. Use a clearly non-production local
# value; a real deployment sets the provisioned workspace's crypto.randomUUID()
# id (see docs/development/DATA_KERNEL.md). Create the matching local workspace
# row before the resolver will succeed locally.
DEFAULT_WORKSPACE_ID="local-dev-workspace"
